The All Progressives Congress (APC), on Saturday, took its presidential campaign to Akure, capital of Ondo state. Bola Tinubu, the APC presidential candidate, and Rotimi Akeredolu, governor of the state, were present at the rally. Other APC governors present at the rally include Dapo Abiodun, Ogun governor, and Babajide Sanwo-Olu, his Lagos counterpart. Tinubu also inaugurated the south-west campaign office. Below are photos:                      